<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Themis on 04-16-2001 06:45 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">As a common rule of thumb for the majority of raids against mobs that dispell, you usually throw, generally speaking, 'useless' buffs on first, and the important ones last. (Useless as defined: endure cold/poison/disease against Lord Nagafen). This allows those 'useless' buffs to get taken down first, while leaving the good stuff behind . Kinda like the question: How many licks DOES it take to get to the center of a tootsie pop?

Well, after playing around the idea for a bit, and teaming up with my pullers who seem to always get dispelled, I got this idea. Why not do the same thing nin normal groups where dispells fly like crazy. Problem is, that takes up alot of mana after awhile. So, why not have items that cast buffs do that as well?

For myself, I buff myself with Deadeye from my Paineel quested fright forged helm, See invisibility from my bracer of the hidden, and my Jman's boots. 3 buffs (2 if inside) that can easily be replaced without the cost of mana. Cause those Symbols of Naltron get pretty expensive being dispelled quickly, I began looking for items that will be able to buff others.

What items are out there that can be used to do this? The only item I have to buff others with is the Bracer of the Hidden. Any more ideas?

Thanks in advance!

------------------
[51 Vicar] Themis Silverlight (Human) 
[b][URL=http://www.thevigilant.net/]Dark Vigilance[/URL][/b]
Agnostic Cleric
[URL=http://www.innoruuk.com/]Innoruuk[/URL] Server</TEXTAREA>
